The National Commissioner of the Independent National Electoral Commissioner (INEC) in charge of Kogi, Kwara and Nasarawa, Mohammed Haruna on Saturday assured that the electoral umpire would be transparent and fair in ongoing recall process of Senator Dino Melaye.

Mohammed who spoke after monitoring the exercise in Lokoja said the Commission as an umpire was only carrying out its mandate required by the Electoral Act and has no special interest whatsoever in whoever loses or wins at the end of the day.Â 

He said he was impressed with the peaceful conduct of the exercise so far.